  "27": {
    "inputs": {
      "value": "A fine-art figure study of a single seated woman, composed in the tradition of classical painterly nude photography, emphasizing form, light, and gesture rather than display. She is posed three-quarter-turned away from the camera on a simple wooden stool, her back and the curve of her shoulder toward the lens, head tilted gently downward so her face is in soft profile shadow, one arm drawn across to rest a hand on the opposite knee in a quiet, self-contained pose. Long hair falls loosely across one shoulder. A length of soft draped linen pools across her lap and the stool, the fabric doing the work of the composition. The setting is a bare studio with a seamless deep-charcoal backdrop. Single large softbox positioned high and to the left as a directional key, raking low across her form to sculpt the topography of the spine, shoulder blade, and the muscles of the back into gentle gradients of light and shadow — strong chiaroscuro, a luminous highlight along the lit edge falling into deep shadow on the far side. A subtle cool rim light traces her silhouette on the right. Skin rendered with natural texture, no glamour gloss. Shot on an 85mm lens, f/4, ISO 100, studio strobe. The warm tonality, fine grain, and gentle highlight roll-off of Kodak Portra 400. Restrained, sculptural, timeless black-and-white-leaning fine-art photography."
    },
    "class_type": "PrimitiveStringMultiline",
    "_meta": {
      "title": "Text String (Multiline)"
